Bank of Japan Keeps Key Interest Rate Near 0%, Credit Programs Unchanged

-- B y   K e i k o   U j i k a n e
-- 
2011-07-12T04:21:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-12/bank-of-japan-keeps-key-interest-rate-near-0-credit-programs-unchanged.html
The  Bank of Japan (8301)  held the benchmark
interest rate at a range of zero to 0.1 percent and kept
unchanged a 30-trillion yen ($375 billion) credit program and a
10-trillion yen asset-purchase fund that represent its main
policy tools. The central bank announced its policy decision in
a statement today in  Tokyo .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Keiko Ujikane in Tokyo at 
 kujikane@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gearoid Reidy at 
 greidy1@bloomberg.net  